'''Meerwein芳基化反应'''（Meerwein arylation），由 Hans Meerwein 在1939年报道。

[[芳基|芳基]][[重氮盐|重氮盐]]在金属盐类存在下对缺电子[[烯烃|烯烃]]的加成反应。产物为取代芳香族化合物。<ref>[[Hans_Meerwein|Meerwein, H]];, Buchner, E.; van Emsterk, K. ''[[J._Prakt._Chem.|J. Prakt. Chem.]]'' '''1939''', 152, 237.</ref><ref>''Minireview Intermolecular Olefin Functionalisation Involving Aryl Radicals Generated from Arenediazonium Salts''  Markus R. Heinrich {{DOI|10.1002/chem.200801306}} Chemistry - A European Journal 2008 Volume 15 Issue 4, Pages 820 - 833</ref>

[[Image:Meerwein_arylation.png|400px]]

烯烃上的[[吸电子基团|吸电子基团]]降低了烯烃双键的电子密度。

==反应机理==
反应的具体机理仍不清楚。<ref>''Strategic Applications of Named Reactions in Organic Synthesis'' Laszlo Kurti, Barbara Czako Academic Press (March 4, '''2005''') ISBN 0-12-429785-4</ref> 

有认为此反应为[[自由基-亲核芳香取代|自由基-亲核芳香取代]]机理。首先重氮盐断裂放出氮气，生成[[芳基自由基|芳基自由基]]，接下来芳基自由基对双键进行[[自由基加成|自由基加成]]，产生的烷基自由基中间体被重氮盐中的反离子如卤素或[[四氟硼酸根|四氟硼酸根]]捕获，生成取代芳香族化合物。此产物还可继续经过消除放出卤化氢，从而进一步得到苯乙烯衍生物。

==拓展==
1、[[丙烯酸|丙烯酸]]与芳基重氮盐、[[溴化亚铜|溴化亚铜]]和[[氢溴酸|氢溴酸]]反应生成α-溴羧酸<ref>''Benzenepropanoic acid, 4-acetyl-α-bromo-'' [[Organic_Syntheses|Organic Syntheses]], Coll. Vol. 6, p.21 (1988); Vol. 51, p.1 ('''1971'''). [http://www.orgsynth.org/orgsyn/pdfs/CV6P0021.pdf Link] {{Wayback|url=http://www.orgsynth.org/orgsyn/pdfs/CV6P0021.pdf |date=20120205194120 }}</ref>

2、[[丁二烯|丁二烯]]经过反应首先生成4-氯-2-丁烯，再经消除，可得芳基取代的丁二烯<ref>''1,3-Butadiene, 1-(p-nitrophenyl)-'' [[Organic_Syntheses|Organic Syntheses]], Coll. Vol. 4, p.727 ('''1963'''); Vol. 31, p.80 ('''1951'''). [http://www.orgsynth.org/orgsyn/pdfs/CV4P0727.pdf  Link] {{Wayback|url=http://www.orgsynth.org/orgsyn/pdfs/CV4P0727.pdf |date=20120205194132 }}</ref> 

3、还原芳基化：[[三氯化钛|三氯化钛]]将新生成的双键还原<ref>''2-Butanone, 4-(4-chlorophenyl)-'' [[Organic_Syntheses|Organic Syntheses]], Coll. Vol. 7, p.105 (1990); Vol. 62, p.67 ('''1984''') [http://www.orgsynth.org/orgsyn/pdfs/CV7P0105.pdf Link] {{Wayback|url=http://www.orgsynth.org/orgsyn/pdfs/CV7P0105.pdf |date=20120208144004 }}.</ref> 

4、千克级无金属 Meerwein 芳基化<ref>''A Practical Synthesis of -Aryl Methyl Ketones via a Transition-Metal-Free Meerwein Arylation'' Carmela Molinaro, Jeffrey Mowat, Francis Gosselin, Paul D. O'Shea, Jean-François Marcoux, Rémy Angelaud, and Ian W. Davies [[J._Org._Chem.|J. Org. Chem.]]; '''2007'''; 72(5) pp 1856 - 1858; (Note) {{DOI|10.1021/jo062483g}}</ref>

